      <description>&lt;!-- [DocumentBodyStart:e9dd8f29-dea8-450d-89bd-5c9d8970b4cc] --&gt;&lt;div class="jive-rendered-content"&gt;&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;"&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m a zenoss newbie and have just recently started evaluating core 3.1.0.&lt;span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"&gt;&amp;#160; &lt;/span&gt;I have Linux Monitor installed (as well as Linux Monitor Addon) and have a question regarding OSprocess objects that are detected on servers in the &lt;strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"&gt;&lt;em style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal;"&gt;/Server/SSH/Linux&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; class, which is added by this Zenpack.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri;"&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve found that OSprocess objects are detected correctly when a server is modeled, but operational status is not detected &amp;ndash; i.e. a monitored process can fail and the OSprocess object will still indicate green/no events.&lt;span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"&gt;&amp;#160; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;"&gt;Also, the graphs for the OSprocesses are all empty, with the stats indicating &amp;ldquo;nan&amp;#8221;.&lt;span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"&gt;&amp;#160; &lt;/span&gt;This much I can understand, as the default OSprocess monitor template only has SNMP data sources defined.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;"&gt;So my questions are (all questions assue that only SSH-based monitoring is being used):&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 leve